===============================
Compilation and execution of
Ginga 2.0
===============================

-------------------------------
Compilation
-------------------------------

The steps necessaries to build Ginga.ar 2.0 in Linux machine are:


Install the dependencies on Ubuntu:
    Boost
    XERCESC
    EV
    DB
    GTK2
    GDK-PIXBUF
    GLIB PANGO
    CAIRO
    LIBSOUP2
    WEBKIT
    LIBVLC
    LUA
    CURL


The steps to build, inside the folder where the source was decompress:

    cd build
    <Modify the build script "build.ginga.sh">
    ./build.ginga.sh --build


Once the build process is over, in UNIX/bin/ginga the binary of ginga.ar is found.
For more option edit the configuration build files.


-------------------------------
Run an NCLua application
-------------------------------

On the console:
    ginga --ncl application_path.ncl


